---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Services" description="Suspension setup, custom valving, chassis engineering, and track support services from Too Fast To Race.">
  
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="stripe-accent"></span>
      <h1>Our <span class="text-green">Services</span></h1>
      <p class="hero-subtitle">From dyno testing to trackside support – comprehensive suspension and chassis services for every level of motorsport.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Service: Suspension Setup -->
  <section id="suspension" class="service-detail">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="service-header">
        <span class="service-number">01</span>
        <h2>Suspension Setup & Development</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="service-grid">
        <div class="service-content">
          <p class="lead">Your car is unique. Your setup should be too.</p>
          <p>Whether you're preparing for track days, hillclimbs, or simply want your road car to handle better, we develop suspension setups tailored to your specific needs, driving style, and application.</p>
          
          <h4>What's Included:</h4>
          <ul class="service-list">
            <li>Complete damper assessment and dyno testing</li>
            <li>Spring rate selection and matching</li>
            <li>Ride height optimisation</li>
            <li>Corner weight adjustment</li>
            <li>Data-driven development using AiM equipment</li>
            <li>Before/after comparison testing</li>
          </ul>
          
          <p>We work with all major damper brands including Penske, Nitron, Ohlins, and Quantum. Even if you didn't buy your dampers from us, we can service and optimise them.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-features">
          <div class="feature-card">
            <h5>Track Setup</h5>
            <p>Race-focused configurations for maximum grip and predictable handling at the limit.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-card">
            <h5>Road Setup</h5>
            <p>Comfortable, controlled, and engaging. Performance without compromise on daily usability.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-card">
            <h5>Hillclimb Specific</h5>
            <p>Optimised for the unique demands of hillclimb – fast direction changes and varied surfaces.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Service: Custom Valving -->
  <section id="valving" class="service-detail alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="service-header">
        <span class="service-number">02</span>
        <h2>Custom Valving</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="service-grid reverse">
        <div class="service-features">
          <div class="feature-card">
            <h5>Linear Valving</h5>
            <p>Consistent damping force throughout the stroke. Ideal for smooth surfaces and predictable handling.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-card">
            <h5>Digressive Valving</h5>
            <p>Better compliance over bumps while maintaining high-speed control. Our recommended option for most Caterhams.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-card">
            <h5>Progressive Valving</h5>
            <p>Increasing damping with speed. Excellent for cars that see both road and track use.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="service-content">
          <p class="lead">We're not all the same. Why should your suspension be?</p>
          <p>Suspension feel is subjective. What works for one driver may not suit another. Custom valving allows us to tune your dampers specifically for YOU – your weight, your driving style, your preferences.</p>
          
          <p>Every set of dampers we valve is built to order. We'll discuss your requirements, build the shim stacks to suit, then dyno test to verify performance before shipping.</p>
          
          <h4>The Process:</h4>
          <ul class="service-list">
            <li>Consultation on your requirements and driving style</li>
            <li>Piston and shim stack specification</li>
            <li>Assembly with fresh oil and seals</li>
            <li>Dyno testing and verification</li>
            <li>Setup recommendations and adjustment guide</li>
          </ul>
          
          <p>We particularly recommend digressive front pistons for Caterhams – they transform turn-in feel and ride quality over larger bumps.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Service: Chassis Engineering -->
  <section id="chassis" class="service-detail">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="service-header">
        <span class="service-number">03</span>
        <h2>Chassis Engineering</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="service-grid">
        <div class="service-content">
          <p class="lead">Suspension doesn't exist in isolation.</p>
          <p>A properly set up car is more than just good dampers. It's about how every component works together – geometry, springs, anti-roll bars, ride height, and weight distribution all contribute to the complete package.</p>
          
          <p>Our chassis engineering service takes a holistic approach. We assess your car as a complete system and develop solutions that address the whole picture, not just individual components.</p>
          
          <h4>Chassis Services:</h4>
          <ul class="service-list">
            <li>Geometry measurement and optimisation</li>
            <li>Corner weighting and balance adjustment</li>
            <li>Anti-roll bar selection and setup</li>
            <li>Ride height calibration</li>
            <li>Bump steer correction</li>
            <li>Caster, camber, and toe optimisation</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="service-features">
          <div class="feature-card highlight">
            <h5>Complete Assessment</h5>
            <p>Full chassis evaluation with detailed report on current state and recommended improvements.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-card">
            <h5>Setup Day</h5>
            <p>Bring your car in for a full day of chassis setup and optimisation. Leave with a transformed driving experience.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-card">
            <h5>Development Programme</h5>
            <p>Ongoing chassis development with iterative testing and refinement for serious competitors.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Service: Track Support -->
  <section id="track" class="service-detail alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="service-header">
        <span class="service-number">04</span>
        <h2>Track & Event Support</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="service-grid reverse">
        <div class="service-features">
          <div class="feature-card">
            <h5>Trackside Setup</h5>
            <p>Real-time adjustments based on track conditions and your feedback between sessions.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-card">
            <h5>Data Analysis</h5>
            <p>Review your logged data to identify setup improvements and driving optimisations.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-card">
            <h5>Technical Support</h5>
            <p>Problem solving and emergency repairs. We've seen most issues before and know how to fix them quickly.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="service-content">
          <p class="lead">Sometimes you need help at the track.</p>
          <p>Whether you're competing in a championship or enjoying a track day, having experienced technical support can make the difference between a frustrating weekend and a successful one.</p>
          
          <p>We offer trackside support at events across the UK. This includes setup consultation, real-time adjustments between sessions, data review, and technical problem solving.</p>
          
          <h4>Available For:</h4>
          <ul class="service-list">
            <li>Caterham Championship support</li>
            <li>Hillclimb and sprint events</li>
            <li>Track days and testing sessions</li>
            <li>Race weekend support</li>
          </ul>
          
          <p>Contact us to discuss your event requirements. We're particularly well set up for Caterham competitors but welcome enquiries for other lightweight sports cars.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="cta-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="cta-content">
        <h2>Ready to Improve Your Setup?</h2>
        <p>Get in touch to discuss your requirements. No obligation – just a conversation about what you're looking to achieve.</p>
        <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Get In Touch</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
  /* Page Hero */
  .page-hero {
    padding: calc(80px + var(--space-xl)) 0 var(--space-lg);
    background: var(--tftr-darker);
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(92, 184, 92, 0.2);
  }

  .hero-subtitle {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--tftr-grey-light);
    max-width: 60ch;
    margin-top: var(--space-sm);
  }

  /* Service Detail Sections */
  .service-detail {
    background: var(--tftr-black);
    scroll-margin-top: 80px;
  }

  .service-detail.alt {
    background: var(--tftr-darker);
  }

  .service-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .service-number {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(3rem, 8vw, 5rem);
    color: var(--tftr-green);
    opacity: 0.3;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .service-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.5fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-xl);
    align-items: start;
  }

  .service-grid.reverse {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.5fr;
  }

  .service-grid.reverse .service-features {
    order: -1;
  }

  .service-content .lead {
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    color: var(--tftr-white);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .service-content p {
    color: var(--tftr-grey-light);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .service-content h4 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    color: var(--tftr-green);
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .service-list {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .service-list li {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    color: var(--tftr-grey-light);
  }

  .service-list li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.6em;
    width: 8px;
    height: 2px;
    background: var(--tftr-green);
  }

  .service-features {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-md);
  }

  .feature-card {
    padding: var(--space-md);
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--tftr-green);
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }

  .feature-card:hover {
    background: rgba(92, 184, 92, 0.05);
    border-color: rgba(92, 184, 92, 0.3);
  }

  .feature-card.highlight {
    background: rgba(92, 184, 92, 0.1);
    border-color: var(--tftr-green);
  }

  .feature-card h5 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
  }

  .feature-card p {
    color: var(--tftr-grey-light);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* CTA Section */
  .cta-section {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--tftr-green-dark), var(--tftr-green));
    text-align: center;
  }

  .cta-content h2 {
    color: var(--tftr-black);
  }

  .cta-content p {
    color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7);
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin: var(--space-sm) auto var(--space-md);
    max-width: 50ch;
  }

  .cta-content .btn-primary {
    background: var(--tftr-black);
    color: var(--tftr-white);
  }

  .cta-content .btn-primary:hover {
    background: var(--tftr-darker);
  }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .service-grid,
    .service-grid.reverse {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .service-grid.reverse .service-features {
      order: 0;
    }

    .service-header {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: var(--space-xs);
    }
  }
</style>
